lec-114 - Primitive data types in JS
-------------------------------------
There are 5 primitive datatypes in JS.

1. Numbers
-----------
4 -whole number
3.4 -fractional number
100
-10 -negative

All types of numbers are categorized as the same type of numbers.

2.Strings
----------
"hello world"
"43"

3.Boolean
----------
true
false

4.null and undefined
-----------------------
these are actually values

____________________
Lect116- VAriables
_________________________

The variables in JS are declared simply with prefix var, they do not have any datatype.

var name = "Allwyn"
var age = 32
var permanent = true
var address = null    --- explicitly says, no value for the variable.
var stren = undefined --- means that the value for the variable is not yet defined, it can be defined in future.

JS variables should be camelCased.

