lect- 155
----------

Javascript Array Methods:
--------------------------
1. push() - adds a value in the end of an array.
2. pop() - removes a value from the end of an array.
3.unshift() - adds a value to the front of an array.
4.shift() - removes the value from the front of an array.
5.Locate a value in an array - friends.indexOf("David"); If there are same 2 values in the array then the first instance is returned. If the element is not present then -1 is returned.
6. The slice(start, end) creates a new array with contents of an existing array (as per the index mentioned in the slice method). The original array is not affected in any ways.
e.g. var friends = ['David', 'Moses', 'Iseah', 'John', 'Mathew'];
     var nufriends = friends.slice(1,3)
     nuFriends = ['Moses', 'Iseah', 'John'] 	
the slice method can also be used to copy an entire array.





